tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating impaired glucose metabolism or possible prediabetes, despite normal fasting glucose. Creatinine is slightly below normal, which is generally not clinically significant. Total CO₂ is mildly decreased, suggesting possible mild metabolic acidosis or compensation. Other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation and monitoring of glycemic control.
